    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Less Than Universal</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Michael Miles letter comments on Sept 14 article on remote control devices</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To The Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Ultimate Remote Means Never Having To Leave the Couch'' (Sept. 14), about controls that handle many devices:</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To The Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Ultimate Remote Means Never Having To Leave the Couch'' (Sept. 14), about controls that handle many devices:</p>
        <p>The universal remote control is a great invention, but please let me know if any of these behemoths can be set to program my VCR to record a future program, not just to perform the basic features of a standard VCR. Of all the universal remote controls I have seen, none have been able to prevent me from having to dig out the original VCR-only remote control to program my VCR to record a program taking place at a later point in time.</p>
        <p>MICHAEL MILES  New York</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
